{
  "stem": "18626.10",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 303.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I discussed-- my brother decided to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my sister, Miriam, decided to go to Israel, too.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they went to Israel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, it was very hard [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] separation.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I knew we are not going in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] We can all the time meet-- anytime we want, we can meet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was at that time already an old man, 21 years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After I was in Sankt Ottilien, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] two, I think, majors-- American majors in a jeep arrived in Sankt Ottilien.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they told the chief, you know, from the hospitals that they got to interview people who were in Dachau because there's going to start a trial against 40 the biggest Nazis who carried on in Dachau, the commandant with all the big shots, the murderers.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there's going to start a trial.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they need important witnesses who saw, who lived, who knew certain things and can speak out, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they start to interview a lot of people, you know, in different-- first, in different DP camps and in hospitals.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then they came to my hospital in Sankt Ottilien.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they interviewed one room, another room, another room.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then they ask voluntarily, who wants to come for interview to be a witness in Dachau?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said, I was in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I want to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I would like to be interviewed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It would be my biggest pleasure.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I hate to say that word, 'revenge.' But I must say that would be the best thing in my life if I can meet eye-on-eye with the commandant from Dachau and look him in the eyes.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
